#Text=Ontario Votes 2007 : Interview with Freedom Party candidate Wayne
#Text=Simmons , Don Valley East
#Text=Wednesday , October 3 , 2007
#Text=Wayne Simmons is running for the Freedom Party in the Ontario provincial election , in the Don Valley East riding .
#Text=Wikinews ' Nick Moreau interviewed him regarding his values , his experience , and his campaign .

#Text=The question has smuggled into it a collectivist premise that a Politician is some kind of Rousseuian grand legislator who has mystical insight into the  General Will " of his community .

column1: #Text=Many people are concerned about excessive taxation .
#Text=Many are concerned about the lack of choice in Education and Healthcare .
#Text=What should be the first order of business in the 39th Legislative Assembly ?
#Text=Cutting taxes , specifically , property and income taxes .
#Text=Are the property taxes in your riding at a fair level for the amount of services received in the municipality ?
#Text=No.
#Text=There is no " fair " level .
#Text=Who can determine the " fair " level ?
#Text=This question presupposes some kind mystical collective way of determining fairness with regard to taxation .
#Text=How can the province lead the way in stimulating job creation ?
#Text=Abolish the provincial income tax and scrap property taxes , for starters .
#Text=What are your views on the mixed member proportional representation ( MMP ) referendum ?
#Text=MMP would make majority Governments difficult - if not impossible .

#Text=It is only by Freedom Party forming a majority Government where the necessary uncompromising changes can be made to restore Government respect for the individual 's right to life , liberty and property .
#Text=What role , if any , does " new media " play in your campaign , and the campaign of your party ?
#Text=( websites , blogs , Facebook , YouTube videos , etc ) Do you view it as beneficial , or a challenge ?
#Text=They 're all beneficial .
#Text=The party uses practically all methods of new media .
